Nov 20 2009 	Fabulous location	On arriving at 9.30am to drop off our bags, Ryan went out of his way to get us checked in 3 hours early. The same level of helpfulness was evident in all members of staff. The decor is totally OTT: huge chandeliers, lots of gilt plasterwork; sweeping staircases and period features. - I love it, but it may not be to everyone's taste. The rooms were clean and the bed comfy. Coffee machines are availble on request, we only found this out when one was delivered to our room in error one morning.The location on Union Square is superb, with the trolley cars passing the front door, most bus lines within a block, Walgreen opposite for those bits you forgot and Starbucks tucked into a corner for coffee and muffins in the morning (you dont' have to leave the hotel if you use the back entrance). We thought the food and drink was quite expensive, but who want to stay inthe hotel when there are so many alternatives on the doorstep.All in all a great experience and I would definitely stay there again.	
