Jul 23 2009 	Manage your expectations then enjoy...	We traveled to SF on leisure in mid-June. We had some mix-ups on our airline reservations and found ourselves needing a hotel for an extra evening. Unfortunately this extra evening practically double the price of the room, and so at a related-Kimpton hotel, our reservationist recommended Sir Francis Drake. We did what most do, went online and read Trip Advisor, all the reviews, considered location (EXCELLENT!) and price, and decided it was worth the risk. Our first trip to SF we asked for a view that would be suggested, and booked a King room. Check-in was a breeze, the room (2008) was simply incredible (check out pictures) - and yes, was the room small compared to newer hotels? Sure. Was the bathroom small? Sure. Did it cause us to get out and enjoy our vacation? SURE!The location, the views, the courteous staff, concierge with bus and train information - all were bonuses. We were actually warned about the club being right above us, and yes one evening we had our own celebration in our room with a little bass for effect - and didn't have a problem with it. Eddy the beefeater was amazing, great tips and tricks for everything we asked. He earned his tip for sure, and PLEASE check with the beefeater for bus tickets, etc that may not be used up before you buy...Is the hotel new? No, but it doesn't advertise to be such. Is it clean? We didn't have any issues at all. Was there paint peeling? Sure, in a few places - but determine your reservations on what your expectations are, then enjoy your time! Our room may have been a little small for our entire family, but it was PERFECT for just us 2. We will definitely stay again!	
