Mar 28 2009 	Good price and perfect location	The Drake is a perfectly located hotel, that is not bad value for money. I stayed here with my girlfriend for several nights and for the right price, would stay again.The hotel is perfectly located. There's a cable car line on your doorstep, and several major stores lie a matter of minutes away. San Francisco isn't huge, and if you don't mind spending the day on your feet, most of the major sights are within walking distance. The downside of this, was being woken up by general noise or sirens every morning.Hotel has a grand lobby and staff were all extremely courteous. They checked us in early, free of charge, and the concierge arranged several excursions for us.Our room was tiny, but clean and the bathroom was adequate. Walls were paper thin however, and we were woken one night to a drunk &quot;neighbour&quot; screaming obscenities.If you want to stay central without spending all your money on accommodation, the Drake is a perfect option.For people on their first trip to the US and looking to enjoy a &quot;big&quot; American meal, I recommend the Cheescake Factory (two minutes from the Drake). Don't be offput by the name, they serve an array of foods, and it is one of very few restaurants I have eaten at where I couldn't finish my dish.	
