Jan 7 2008 	Great location!	I booked my room at the Drake during Kimpton's 24-hour sale and got a rate of $99/night (and that included New Years Eve!) For that rate---literally steps away from Union Square in San Francisco...it is difficult to say anything negative. I stayed 3-nights on a business/pleasure trip during the holiday. I stay at Kimpton's because they are comfortable, dog friendly and usually have great restaurants/room service. The Drake isn't one of their newer properties, but it is nicely decorated. As some have said, it is showing its age---but is has been maintained. The location cannot be beat! The hotel is next door to the Saks in Union Square. It is across the street from the famous Sear's restaurant (the ever present line moves quickly- it is worth the short wait.) Note: If you are able to get a good rate at the Drake- you will not find a better location!I found the friendliness of the staff to be 50-50. Some were very friendly and helpful---others couldn't be bothered. This could have had something to do with it being a holiday. The hotel was obviously very busy.Upon arrival I found that they didn't have my Kimpton number in my reservation (even though I had made the reservation through their site.) I did not receive the usual welcome amenities, robes, etc. I was traveling with a pet and usually they will bring up a bed, water bowls, etc. None of this was provided. They were so busy I didn't bother worrying about it. Hey, I paid $99...I wasn't going to freak out over a robe and a bottle of water. :)The room service menu is limited and it stops at 11PM (although I was told by the operator they stop taking orders at 10:30PM.) They also closed at 2PM on New Years Day. Nice for their workers...a bit of a hassle for guests planning on staying in that night. I stayed in room 1204. There was zero street noise and the hallways were very quiet.The standard free wireless worked great in both the lobby and room. The work area in the room was comfortable. The cable worked fine. They provide standard channels, but no movie channel (HBO, Showtime, etc.)The bathroom amenities are a basic brand (not the L'Occitane that you find at some of their other hotels.) They were well stocked. The linens and towels were good quality. The beds and pillows are very comfortable. The mattress is soft and comfy---which I love. However, if you are looking for a really firm mattress...this might not be the place for you.Valet is $44 + tax/ night. They say to call down 40 minutes before you need your car. Call early...It took them an hour and 15 minutes to bring my car. It is Union Square and traffic is tough...plan ahead. While I didn't find the Drake to be a typical Kimpton...it is certainly a decent hotel. The location is great, comfortable beds, free wireless---if you can get a good rate---there is no reason not to stay at this hotel. Definitely a great hotel for tourists!	
