Sep 19 2007 	Love the Drake!	We stayed at the Drake for 4 nights in September. I was slightly worried before we got there because we were due to arrive in the evening after a very long journey from the UK. I was very pleased with what we found. Check in was quick and easy, the room was extremely comfortable and charming, the shower was brilliant. I really can't think of anything to complain about! I'm very suprised there are negative reviews on here, but then they seem to be mainly about individual rooms. Ours was on the 3rd floor and we had no real problems at all. We found the staff to be really friendly and helpful, they booked our tickets to Alcatraz for us and gave us plenty of maps and directions. The location was fantastic. There are shops and restaurants nearby, and right outside you can get the tram down to the pier. I would recommend doing this once, but after that there is a very good bus service which is faster and cheaper. I worked out the bus routes from a map I got from the hotel lobby. We had breakfast once at the caffe espresso directly next door, which was very nice, and also once at Sears across the road (make sure you're hungry!). Over all, I would definitely recommend the Drake to others as a good budget hotel. I'm really glad we stayed there. And I love San Francisco! p.s loved the beefeaters too!	
