Sep 3 2007	Honeymoon	The Sir Francis Drake met my expectations from what I read from other reviews. It is an old hotel with a lot of character. It is centrally located in the Union Square area. It is within walking distance of Union Square shpping and attactions. We had a Queen Deluxe room (the bed was a king so we may have had an upgrade). It was reasonably large with a walk-in closet. The room decor was very nice. There was some cracked paint on the ceiling but this did not bother us (it added to the hotel's character). Based on other reviews, I expected this and think cracked paint is pretty common. The rooms were otherwise clean and in good order. The bed was very comfortable.The cable cars stop in front of the hotel but they are often full before they reach this stop. If we were going to the Fisherman's Warf, we would walk to Market street and take a street car. It is much easier to catch cable cars on the return trip. The Starlight Room is a nice nightclub with great city views. Contrary to other information I received, the dress code is now casual, and a jacket and tie are no longer required.	
