Jan 10 2007 	Great location - Clean - Classy	This hotel is located right downtown in the Union Square area, very close to great shopping and dining. We stayed in a queen room which was surprisingly small. Very little extra room for anything, such as large suitcases or the in-room yoga program the hotel advertised. The bathroom was also very small. However, this hotel is undergoing renovations, and our room had been redone very recently. The furnishing were stylish and modern, the bed was VERY comfortable, the room had high-speedwireless internet, large TV, quality pillows, AVEDA bath products and plush robes. I enjoyed staying here because everything was clean and comfortable and new. I do wish the room had been a little larger - my sister and I found ourselves chatting after dinner in the lobby rather than our room because it was too small and confining. The concierge was great with restaurant recommendations. Also, watch out for the $45 dollar/day parking charge!	
Dec 20 2006 	First Class Hotel	We didnt stay here but did a sight inspection as part of work (I am a travel agent).The Sir Francis Drake Hotel is part of the United States largest boutique hotel chain – Kimpton Hotels. This property has a ‘First Class’ rating which I believe it deserves. It is located in Union Square and has a wide variety of shops, restaurants and cafes within walking distance.Rooms are of a smallish size, with striped décor (Cream/Sage). The hotel also offers a &quot;Mind. Body. Spa&quot; program with in-room spa services, Yoga channel on every TV and complimentary yoga accessories for use during clients stay. Sir Francis Drake Hotel also has its own luxury nightclub – Starlight Room. This nightclub/bar offers fantastic views of San Francisco.The Powell/Hyde cable car goes straight past the entrance of this hotel so it is also very easy to get to Fisherman’s Wharf and Pier 33.This hotel had a very elegant feel to it and would suit couples, families with older children and business travellers.	
