Apr 20 2006	Stay Somewhere Else	The problem starts when you try to check in and the rooms aren't ready. By the time that the rooms were ready, the entire lobby was filled with guests waiting to check-in. But that still didn't get additional people behind the desk. One of the elevators operated all day with only half of its interior lights working.The rooms are very, very small and very, very shabby. The floor tiles in the bathroom are chipped and missing in places. The finish is mostly gone from the bottom of the tub. The electrical outlets by the desk are too old to handle 3-prong plugs and if you need to plug something in, you have a choice of pulling the plug for the lamp or the refrigerator. The window is coated with dirt. The noise from the street is constant. Every complaint is answered with the same response - we are going to get a multi-million dollar upgrade soon. One of my worst hotel experiences. The location is wonderful, but there are many other hotels in the vicinity that provide better accomodations and service.	
